<HEAD>Tiger Attacks Teen-age Trainer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 176-pound Bengal tiger attacked its 17-year-old
trainer and broke her neck at a show for junior high school
students, police said today.
   The tiger bit Tomiko Omi on Monday when she unchained the animal
to begin the show inside a cage at the Shiratori Zoo in Kagawa,
southwestern Japan, a police official said.
   The official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the tiger
pulled away from Omi when another trainer near the cage shouted
``stop'' and lashed the animal with a whip.
   He said Omi was taken to a hospital with a broken neck and
injuries around her shoulder. But her life was not in immediate
danger, the official said.
   Omi has been a trainer for 21 months, the official said.
</TEXT>
