<LEADPARA>  THE CALVES specially raised to produce a gastronomic delicacy deceptively
named "milk-fed veal" spend their entire lives chained in pens less than 2
feet wide and 5 feet long.;    Those stalls are so small the animals cannot
ever groom themselves, turn around or even lie down in a natural position.
They must walk in their own urine and excrement, and inhale ammonia produced
